HOUSE BILL No. 1280
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning trade
regulation.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 24-5-24.6 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]:
4 Chapter 24.6. Social Security Number Search Requests
5 Sec. 1. This chapter applies to a consumer reporting agency that
6 compiles and maintains files on consumers on a nationwide basis.
7 Sec. 2. (a) As used in this chapter, "consumer" means an
8 individual whose principal residence is in Indiana.
9 (b) The term includes the following:
10 (1) A protected consumer (as defined in IC 24-5-24.5-4).
11 (2) A representative acting on behalf of an individual
12 described in subdivision (1).
13 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "consumer report" means any
14 written, oral, or other communication of any information that:
15 (1) is made by a consumer reporting agency;
16 (2) bears on a consumer's creditworthiness, credit standing,
17 credit capacity, character, general reputation, personal
2026 IN 1280—LS 6956/DI 101

2
1 characteristics, or mode of living; and
2 (3) is used or expected to be used or collected in whole or in
3 part for the purpose of serving as a factor in establishing a
4 consumer's eligibility for credit to be used primarily for
5 personal, family, or household purposes.
6 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "consumer reporting agency"
7 means any person that, for monetary fees or dues, or on a
8 cooperative nonprofit basis, regularly engages in whole or in part
9 in the practice of assembling or evaluating information concerning
10 a consumer's credit or other information for the purpose of
11 furnishing a consumer report to another person.
12 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "consumer reporting agency that
13 compiles and maintains files on consumers on a nationwide basis"
14 has the meaning set forth in 15 U.S.C. 1681a(p).
15 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "file", when used in connection
16 with information on a consumer, means all the information on that
17 consumer that is recorded and retained by a consumer reporting
18 agency, regardless of how the information is stored.
19 Sec. 7. As used in this chapter, "proper identification", with
20 respect to a Social Security number search request, means all of
21 the following for the consumer to whom the request pertains:
22 (1) The consumer's Social Security number.
23 (2) The consumer's first and last name.
24 (3) The consumer's date of birth.
25 Sec. 8. As used in this chapter, "Social Security number search
26 request" refers to a request that:
27 (1) is made by a consumer to a consumer reporting agency in
28 conjunction with a request made under 15 U.S.C. 1681g for
29 information in the consumer's file; and
30 (2) requests that the consumer reporting agency conduct a
31 search of all files maintained by the consumer reporting
32 agency to determine if the consumer's Social Security
33 number:
34 (A) as supplied by the consumer in connection with the
35 request; and
36 (B) as verified by the consumer reporting agency as
37 belonging to the consumer;
38 is associated with one (1) or more files not associated with the
39 consumer.
40 Sec. 9. (a) After December 31, 2026, upon receiving a Social
41 Security number search request from a consumer, a consumer
42 reporting agency shall fulfill the consumer's Social Security
2026 IN 1280—LS 6956/DI 101

3
1 number search request if the consumer reporting agency:
2 (1) maintains a file on the consumer; and
3 (2) receives:
4 (A) proper identification from the consumer; and
5 (B) the consumer's written and signed consent for the
6 consumer reporting agency to verify with the federal
7 Social Security Administration that the consumer's Social
8 Security number belongs to the consumer. A consent that
9 is in an electronic form and that includes the consumer's
10 electronic signature constitutes written and signed consent
11 for purposes of this clause.
12 (b) In fulfilling a Social Security number search request that
13 satisfies the conditions set forth in subsection (a), a consumer
14 reporting agency shall do the following:
15 (1) Verify with the federal Social Security Administration that
16 the Social Security number supplied by the consumer in
17 connection with the request belongs to the consumer.
18 (2) Conduct a search of all files maintained by the consumer
19 reporting agency to determine if the consumer's Social
20 Security number is associated with one (1) or more files not
21 associated with the consumer.
22 (3) Include the following as part of the information provided
23 to the consumer in connection with the consumer's request
24 under 15 U.S.C. 1681g:
25 (A) A statement as to whether the results of the consumer
26 reporting agency's search under subdivision (2) indicate
27 that the consumer's Social Security number is associated
28 with one (1) or more files not associated with the
29 consumer.
30 (B) If the consumer reporting agency's search indicates
31 that the consumer's Social Security number is associated
32 with one (1) or more files not associated with the
33 consumer, the following information:
34 (i) The number of files (not including the consumer's file)
35 associated with the consumer's Social Security number.
36 (ii) An identification of each person that procured a
37 consumer report in connection with each file (not
38 including the consumer's file) associated with the
39 consumer's Social Security number during the one (1)
40 year period immediately preceding the date of
41 submission of the consumer's Social Security number
42 search request. For each person identified, the consumer
